          "username": "bgrzybowski"
        },
        "author_role": "REVIEWER",
        "timestamp": "2019-03-28 11:44:39.000000000",
        "message": "Patch Set 1:\n\nGeneric question/doubt: Centos7 is our secondary platform, RedHat being the primary one. Shouldn't we have dockerfile for the latter one in the first place? I mean i'm aware they are sibling platforms but various differences still apply though.\n\nOr maybe it is the case that we develop using Centos image and rely on ci/cd with redhat image to be a final verification step before merge? Because if we introduce molecule testing on ONAP's ci/cd then i guess we'll be using this Centos image, not RedHat? What about RedHat OAT then?",
        "patchset_number": 1
      },
      {
        "id": "f3df0386313837194214e26f7a891fa0cad6835e",
        "author": {
          "account_id": 5097,
          "name": "Bartek Grzybowski",
